WEBVTT

00:01.169 --> 00:04.505
- Previously on The Riches.
- Travellers?

00:04.538 --> 00:06.640
I-I don't think
we know any Travellers.

00:06.674 --> 00:10.111
You know, my buddies
up in New York, they still
don't think you people exist.

00:10.144 --> 00:12.246
We're gonna have
ourselves a wedding.

00:12.280 --> 00:14.782
Our boy and your girl.

00:14.815 --> 00:17.251
I am the new boss.
He is the old boss.

00:17.285 --> 00:20.088
- [ Bell Ringing ]
- Get over it.

00:22.656 --> 00:24.792
- [ Sam ]
So where are we gonna go?
- Life's a river, kid.

00:24.825 --> 00:26.627
You gotta go
where it takes you.

00:29.530 --> 00:31.399
Come on!

00:31.432 --> 00:34.268
You're in the wrong lane!
Mick! Look out!

00:34.302 --> 00:38.139
[ Linda ]
Shit! Stop!
Oh, my God!

00:38.172 --> 00:39.373
I'm sorry.

00:43.411 --> 00:47.415
The American dream.
We're gonna steal it.

00:47.448 --> 00:51.219
Dougie was looking for work...
as a lawyer.

00:51.252 --> 00:52.820
Ever done in-house?

00:52.853 --> 00:55.089
Hi, Doug Rich.

00:55.123 --> 00:57.758
[ Hugh ]
Panco team,
meet your new legal chief.

00:57.791 --> 01:00.094
Dahlia,
what are you doing here?
I brought you lunch.

01:00.128 --> 01:02.696
Isn't that what every
good little housewife's
supposed to do?

01:02.730 --> 01:05.399
I'm guessin'
you're good at
a lot of things.

01:05.433 --> 01:07.335
I could use
someone like that
around here.

01:07.368 --> 01:09.537
I'll bet you could.

01:12.873 --> 01:15.543
[ Bottle Clatters ]

01:17.311 --> 01:19.280
Been there, done that.

01:19.313 --> 01:20.714
So how do I find you?

01:20.748 --> 01:23.817
[ Cael ]
I'll pick you up.
8:00 tonight.

01:23.851 --> 01:27.455
[ Ginny ]
My being here means
you're a dead man, Wayne Malloy.

01:27.488 --> 01:29.757
I think Dale would be mighty
interested in your address.

01:29.790 --> 01:33.627
What do you want,
Ginny Dannegan?

01:33.661 --> 01:37.831
- Well, look who it is.
- Uh, hi, everybody.

01:37.865 --> 01:39.700
- Who is that?
- This'd be Ken.

01:39.733 --> 01:42.836
- Di Di's fiancé.
- What?

01:45.406 --> 01:49.143
[ Growling ]
[ Man Narrating ]
The African lion,

01:49.177 --> 01:51.179
the second largest of feline
species after the tiger,

01:52.480 --> 01:56.450
hones in on its prey.
[ Growling ]

01:56.484 --> 01:59.420
- What is he doing?
- Oh, he's watching
an animal show with Sam.

01:59.453 --> 02:01.855
You see, apparently
retards really like animals.

02:01.889 --> 02:04.758
He's not a retard.
He's just kinda slow.

02:04.792 --> 02:07.561
Cael, this is all your fault
that he's even here
in the first place.

02:07.595 --> 02:10.331
I'm not the one who signed off
on your bride price.

02:15.903 --> 02:19.540
"I hereby offer my daughter,
Delilah, in marriage to
Kenneth Dannegan...

02:19.573 --> 02:23.611
- in exchange for a bride price
of zero dollars."
- You're on clearance.

02:23.644 --> 02:26.314
Shut up, Cael. This is
not a joke. They could
really hold us to this.

02:26.347 --> 02:27.948
Ginny didn't give me
much choice.

02:27.981 --> 02:30.418
You had a choice.
You could've
told 'em to go to hell.

02:30.451 --> 02:33.354
No, sweetheart. Then Ginny
would rat us out, and Dale
would find us. We had no choice.

02:33.387 --> 02:36.490
I will figure this out.
Just give me
a couple of days.

02:36.524 --> 02:38.492
[ Ken ]
Y-You can watch now.
That zebra's down for the count.

02:40.628 --> 02:44.398
It ain't the lion's fault.
He just needs to kill.

02:46.434 --> 02:48.702
Why does he have to
stay with us?

02:48.736 --> 02:52.506
The fiancé always stays with
the in-laws in the run-up
to the wedding. It's tradition.

02:52.540 --> 02:55.343
I'm not gonna marry him.
It's tradition.
That's all I'm saying.

02:55.376 --> 02:57.445
Goes all the way back to
the Middle Ages in Ireland.

02:57.478 --> 02:59.213
You know?
It's your heritage!
[ Sighs ]

02:59.247 --> 03:02.450
We should never have signed
that bride price, Wayne.

03:02.483 --> 03:04.418
Should've just killed Ginny.

03:04.452 --> 03:06.854
If you just let me get through
the arbitration tomorrow,
I will deal with this.

03:06.887 --> 03:10.658
- Arbi-what?
- It's a legal term, Ken.

03:10.691 --> 03:13.461
Well, I better learn it up if
I'm gonna apprentice with you.

03:13.494 --> 03:15.729
Oh, the son-in-law always
apprentices with the father.

03:15.763 --> 03:18.832
- It's tradition.
- I can blacktop real good.

03:18.866 --> 03:21.602
[ Can Opens ]

03:21.635 --> 03:23.737
Look, Ken, this is
a major corporation.

03:23.771 --> 03:26.640
These are educated people.
They-They have law degrees.

03:26.674 --> 03:29.277
They got--
They got M.B.A.'s.

03:30.844 --> 03:34.748
An M.B.A. is
a master's degree
in business administration.

03:34.782 --> 03:36.550
You following me?

03:37.985 --> 03:40.954
A degree is a level of l--
Oh, just forget it, all right?

03:40.988 --> 03:43.757
I guess I could
tarpaper the roof.

03:43.791 --> 03:48.028
No, Ken, you nitwit, this is
a multimillion-dollar lawsuit.

03:48.061 --> 03:50.864
Nobody is tarpapering anything.
You clear?

03:50.898 --> 03:53.334
- You're not coming
to work with me tomorrow.
- That's not what Ginny said.

03:53.367 --> 03:55.436
She said, uh,
if-- if she gets mad,

03:55.469 --> 03:58.572
she's gonna tell the cops
about Mrs. Malloy
violatin' her parole.

04:03.844 --> 04:06.780
The word's "arbitration,"
Ken.

04:06.814 --> 04:09.383
[ Slowly ]
Arbitration.

04:09.417 --> 04:14.455
- It means a polite argument.
- You sure are pretty, Delilah.

04:15.956 --> 04:17.758
[ Sam ]
Ken, he's gonna eat a warthog.

04:17.791 --> 04:20.594
[ Warthog Grunting, Lion Roars ]
Oh, cool.

04:49.957 --> 04:53.694
We can't let
this thing go to trial.

04:53.727 --> 04:58.432
This woman had her arm eaten
by an alligator in her backyard.

04:58.466 --> 05:02.336
She waves her stump at a jury,
she could get 10 million bucks.

05:02.370 --> 05:04.905
- What's the look?
- I'm going to Panco tomorrow.
I told you.

05:04.938 --> 05:07.408
Oh, Jesus, Dahlia.
Not tomorrow.

05:07.441 --> 05:09.443
I got enough problems trying
to get in there with Ken.

05:09.477 --> 05:12.680
If--
[ Sighs ]

05:12.713 --> 05:17.718
No, I just mean I really
want to try and handle this,

05:17.751 --> 05:19.987
settle it.

05:20.020 --> 05:21.789
You know, arbitrate,
like a real lawyer.

05:21.822 --> 05:24.358
I'm actually kind of
good at this--

05:24.392 --> 05:27.495
negotiating,
working the numbers,
working the angles.

05:27.528 --> 05:29.930
- But I could help you.
- I got Aubrey for that.

05:32.099 --> 05:36.404
I mean she's a paralegal.
She's got a legal education.

05:36.437 --> 05:40.374
I know what paralegal means!

05:40.408 --> 05:42.943
Except I didn't go to school,
Wayne.

05:42.976 --> 05:45.045
I don't have a law degree
or an M.B.A.

05:45.078 --> 05:47.147
Did you hear yourself before,
by the way?

05:47.180 --> 05:52.152
What am I supposed to do
while you are so busy workin'
the numbers and the angles?

05:52.185 --> 05:54.588
[ Mouths Word ]
Sit at home and clip coupons?

05:56.089 --> 05:59.427
You know, as it turns out,

05:59.460 --> 06:03.130
I do not know what
a paralegal is, Wayne.

06:03.163 --> 06:06.867
And I don't care!
Screw you!

06:06.900 --> 06:08.902
You are turning into
such an asshole, Wayne.

06:08.936 --> 06:12.139
Like you never been
in a street fight or two?

06:14.475 --> 06:17.110
You got Traveller blood in you.
Can't just walk away from that.

06:17.144 --> 06:19.913
Can't just
wake up in the morning
and pretend to be somebody else,

06:19.947 --> 06:22.550
like all your traditions
don't matter to you no more.

06:22.583 --> 06:25.653
You are spittin'
in the face of our people,
and there will be consequences.

06:25.686 --> 06:27.955
That is superstitious bullshit.

06:27.988 --> 06:30.591
Oh, no, baby.
It's real.

06:30.624 --> 06:32.426
'Cause let me tell you,

06:32.460 --> 06:36.430
sooner or later, someone's
gonna figure out who we are,

06:36.464 --> 06:41.001
and when this ride ends,
it's gonna crash and burn
so hard it'll destroy us.

06:42.836 --> 06:46.006
So you want to
go for a ride?
Okay.

06:46.039 --> 06:48.976
But I'm goin' with you.

06:49.009 --> 06:53.013
'Cause if it ends,
ain't none of us ever gonna
see each other again.

07:02.690 --> 07:05.493
I have somethin' for ya.

07:09.129 --> 07:12.199
Holy shit!
Yeah, read the inscription.

07:17.037 --> 07:20.240
"To Esther. Love, Frank."

07:20.273 --> 07:23.711
Ginny and I stole it off
an old lady in Jacksonville.

07:23.744 --> 07:26.914
Ginny dressed up like a nurse
and pretended to take
her blood pressure.

07:26.947 --> 07:29.650
Meantime, I snuck
into her bedroom--

07:29.683 --> 07:32.152
Oh.
and picked her clean.

07:32.185 --> 07:35.689
Money, jewelry--
I even stole
her false teeth.

07:37.057 --> 07:39.092
That's really touching, Ken.

07:39.126 --> 07:41.228
I'd do anything
for you, Delilah.

07:43.163 --> 07:46.099
Thank you, Ken.

07:46.133 --> 07:49.970
If-If anybody was ever gonna
hurt you, I'd kill them.

07:51.572 --> 07:55.609
Thanks, Ken. I really have
a lot of homework to do.

07:55.643 --> 07:58.679
Rem-Remember the night
at Ginny's weddin'?
We were all dancin'.

08:00.047 --> 08:02.950
You were in a nightgown,
dancing by the fire.

08:02.983 --> 08:06.554
The light just lit up your hair.

08:06.587 --> 08:10.691
You must have been almost nine,
10 years old.

08:12.893 --> 08:14.695
That was the night
I fell in love with you.

08:15.796 --> 08:18.866
Yeah. Ken,

08:18.899 --> 08:22.102
around here
we call that pedophilia.

08:23.871 --> 08:26.874
[ Chuckles ]
You have such a big vocabulary.

08:29.877 --> 08:33.180
- Good night, Ken.
- Sweet dreams.

08:33.213 --> 08:34.982
[ Birds Chirping ]

08:37.184 --> 08:41.088
[ Gasps ]
You been talking
to my daddy?

08:41.121 --> 08:44.324
He don't talk.
He's been gettin' better,
and you know it.

08:44.357 --> 08:47.828
[ Sighs ]
I heard he's been
asking for you.

08:47.861 --> 08:51.064
I heard Ken and Di Di
are engaged.
Is that true?

08:55.135 --> 08:57.638
How did he find her?

09:00.273 --> 09:05.579
Who says he did?
I heard that Daddy wants him
to lead the family...

09:05.613 --> 09:07.581
until he can
bring Wayne back.

09:07.615 --> 09:09.583
Why would I care about that?

09:09.617 --> 09:12.352
'Cause until Wayne comes back,
you'd have all the power,

09:12.385 --> 09:14.321
and it should be mine.

09:14.354 --> 09:17.157
[ Laughs ]

09:20.327 --> 09:23.096
Did you ever really think
your daddy was gonna pick you?

09:23.130 --> 09:26.199
Dale, you know what
he thinks you are?

09:26.233 --> 09:28.335
A sociopath.

09:28.368 --> 09:31.071
You ever hear that word?

09:31.104 --> 09:33.774
I heard it on
a John Wayne Gacy special.

09:35.208 --> 09:37.177
Means you got no conscience.

09:38.912 --> 09:41.348
Means there's
somethin' wrong
with your soul.

09:41.381 --> 09:44.685
[ Breathing Heavily ]
Now, Earl feels
real bad about it.

09:44.718 --> 09:47.955
Blames himself.
But it ain't his fault.

09:47.988 --> 09:50.290
As far I can remember,
you always been evil.

09:51.925 --> 09:54.194
You used to rip the legs off
frogs when you was a kid.

09:55.996 --> 09:57.665
Then you'd burn 'em.
[ Inhales ]

09:59.232 --> 10:01.869
Go ahead, Dale.
Slit my throat.

10:03.737 --> 10:06.674
Wouldn't that be
just like a sociopath?

10:08.676 --> 10:10.811
[ Grunts ]

10:20.420 --> 10:22.222
[ Clatters, Squeaks ]

10:27.761 --> 10:31.832
[ Water Running ]
[ Wayne ]
Ken, once again.

10:33.701 --> 10:38.138
You're my nephew.
My name is Doug.
Dahlia's name is Cherien.

10:38.171 --> 10:41.975
What you are is an intern.
I thought an intern
was like a doctor,

10:42.009 --> 10:44.077
except real good lookin'
and on TV.

10:44.111 --> 10:47.247
Don't say anything, honey.
Okay? You just keep
nice and quiet.

10:47.280 --> 10:49.850
- [ Honking ]
- School bus is here!

10:52.252 --> 10:54.988
So I should call you
Uncle Dan.

10:56.356 --> 10:58.391
Just keep it zipped,
for Christ sakes.

10:58.425 --> 11:00.427
Say nothing, nada, silence.

11:07.968 --> 11:11.138
Goddamn it.
This is such bullshit.
[ Horn Honks ]

11:29.089 --> 11:31.759
[ Chattering ]

11:49.076 --> 11:53.246
So, you're Doug's nephew
from Jacksonville?

11:57.985 --> 12:00.087
[ Wayne ]
Look, I went over
the Underwood files last night,

12:00.120 --> 12:03.256
and I want to talk numbers
with you, 'cause I think
you got a problem.

12:03.290 --> 12:05.292
Good, great.
Yeah, Cherien!

12:05.325 --> 12:08.361
Hi.
You look like
a million bucks.

12:08.395 --> 12:10.931
Oh.
Mmm.
Welcome to Team Hugh.

12:10.964 --> 12:13.033
Let me
show you the ropes.

12:13.066 --> 12:16.036
Hugh, we gotta settle this
before it goes to trial,
right?

12:16.069 --> 12:17.938
It's import--

12:22.910 --> 12:25.813
Ken, get up.

12:25.846 --> 12:27.815
Want you to staple
some things together.

12:27.848 --> 12:30.283
Sure thing, Mr. Malloy.
Dan. Shit.

12:32.252 --> 12:35.222
Want to know a secret?
I never had
a personal assistant before.

12:35.255 --> 12:38.792
My shrink said I should get one.

12:38.826 --> 12:42.229
[ Laughs ]
She said I can't
take care of myself.

12:42.262 --> 12:44.331
You want me
to take care of you?
My secretary couldn't.

12:44.364 --> 12:46.900
That's why I fired her ass.

12:46.934 --> 12:51.238
[ Clears Throat ]
Anyway, uh, that's why
you came here, isn't it?

12:58.979 --> 13:01.248
Or did you come here
so I could squeeze
your tits again?

13:02.615 --> 13:06.119
Oh, no.
I want the 40 grand
plus benefits.

13:06.153 --> 13:08.989
Bullshit, Cherien.
Your husband pulls down
200K a year.

13:09.022 --> 13:11.591
You don't need money.
I think you want to blow me.

13:11.624 --> 13:14.895
Uh--
[ Chuckles ]

13:14.928 --> 13:17.097
[ Laughs ]
Oh, Hugh.

13:17.130 --> 13:20.033
You're right.
I do.

13:20.067 --> 13:22.102
I wanna blow you so bad.

13:22.135 --> 13:24.004
Come on.
Drop your pants.

13:24.037 --> 13:29.877
[ Chuckles ]
Come on. Drop your pants.
Don't be shy.

13:29.910 --> 13:32.846
'Cause I want to take a picture
of your little ding-dong
for my sexual harassment suit.

13:32.880 --> 13:35.415
That way,
I'm never gonna have
to work again!

13:35.448 --> 13:39.186
Jesus, you're a bitch.
You want to tell me
about that job now?

13:39.219 --> 13:43.924
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Pick up my dry cleaning,
fill out my insurance forms...

13:43.957 --> 13:48.628
and find out how the hell
Ducaine Med gets off chargin'
$1,500 for a damn colonoscopy.

13:48.661 --> 13:51.398
Well, I don't
wanna do any
of that either.

13:51.431 --> 13:54.334
[ Chuckles ]
All right.
What do you wanna do, Cherien?

13:55.635 --> 13:59.339
Mmm, I wanna
"feng shooey"
your office.

13:59.372 --> 14:02.142
No wonder you're such
a miserable bastard, man.
You got no flow.

14:02.175 --> 14:04.411
What's that supposed to mean?

14:04.444 --> 14:07.647
Your chi.
It's all out of whack.

14:07.680 --> 14:10.250
I bet you got insomnia.
Nightmares too.

14:10.283 --> 14:13.921
How do you, uh--
How do you know
about this feng shui?

14:13.954 --> 14:17.290
Had some time on my hands
past couple years.

14:17.324 --> 14:21.594
I read a lot
of Oprah magazines.

14:21.628 --> 14:23.330
Mm-hmm.

14:24.431 --> 14:26.533
All right.

14:26.566 --> 14:30.070
You break anything,
I'll wring your goddamn neck.

14:34.241 --> 14:36.076
[ Door Closes ]

14:47.554 --> 14:49.589
Oh.

15:00.133 --> 15:03.070
Hugh, gotta talk to you
about Underwood.

15:03.103 --> 15:06.106
They're gonna be here
in 10 minutes.
Yeah, make her go away.

15:06.139 --> 15:08.308
I think we should
offer two million,
take it or leave it.

15:08.341 --> 15:09.576
What the hell
you talkin' about?

15:09.609 --> 15:12.179
That's one million less than the
old lady got from McDonald's...

15:12.212 --> 15:14.681
-when she was scalded by coffee.
-And two million more
than I'm gonna pay.

15:16.349 --> 15:20.120
Hugh, this woman was gardening
in her backyard.

15:20.153 --> 15:23.156
An alligator grabbed her arm,
dragged her into a reservoir.

15:23.190 --> 15:25.058
She barely got out
with her life.

15:25.092 --> 15:27.460
So? Mmm!

15:27.494 --> 15:29.562
[ Spits, Groans ]

15:29.596 --> 15:32.966
I didn't create alligators.
I'm not God, hmm?

15:33.000 --> 15:36.469
No, but you got eight
Fish and Wildlife citations...

15:36.503 --> 15:38.738
warning you not to build
on an alligator habitat.

15:38.771 --> 15:41.041
So maybe she should have
thought of that...

15:41.074 --> 15:43.310
before she went outside
and started all that
reckless gardening.

15:43.343 --> 15:45.378
Some people
are morons, Doug.

15:45.412 --> 15:47.480
Don't ever
underestimate that.

15:49.516 --> 15:53.186
Hartley Underwood is
a conniving slut who got
exactly what she deserved.

15:53.220 --> 15:54.721
Well, that's
a very good point, Hugh.

15:54.754 --> 15:57.590
I really don't think
a jury's gonna see it that way.
I know.

15:57.624 --> 16:00.460
- So, tank the bitch.
- She got her arm ripped off.

16:00.493 --> 16:04.597
How much more tanked do you
want her? What do you want me
to do, rip the other arm off?

16:04.631 --> 16:07.700
You see? That's exactly
what Stewart said, and Stewart
is collecting unemployment.

16:07.734 --> 16:10.003
I am not giving her
one thin dime.

16:10.037 --> 16:12.572
And if you can't
make her go away,
you can kiss your job good-bye.

16:14.807 --> 16:18.311
Kimmie.
Latte now!

16:29.722 --> 16:32.292
So we got no dirt
on Hartley Underwood?

16:32.325 --> 16:34.594
No. We did
a complete background check.
Not even a speeding ticket.

16:34.627 --> 16:37.164
But if there was dirt on her,
she could have changed her name.

16:37.197 --> 16:39.666
Go down to city hall.
Get her marriage license.

16:39.699 --> 16:42.269
Check for her maiden name,
aliases, anything.

16:42.302 --> 16:44.537
There's gotta be something.

16:44.571 --> 16:46.606
[ Exhales ]

16:56.316 --> 17:00.053
Let me just start by saying
how truly, deeply,

17:00.087 --> 17:03.390
profoundly
sorry we are...

17:03.423 --> 17:08.595
for this really terrible,
unforeseen, devastating--

17:08.628 --> 17:11.798
- Doug, I don't have time
to shovel bullshit.
- Absolutely. Neither do I.

17:11.831 --> 17:15.168
In fact,
I am keenly aware
that time...

17:15.202 --> 17:20.440
is the only thing
that separates us
from the wilderness.

17:20.473 --> 17:23.743
I mean, hell, Ann,
we are the wilderness,
when you think about it.

17:23.776 --> 17:26.113
Because-- 'Cause--
'Cause man versus nature,

17:26.146 --> 17:28.648
that really is a,
uh, false dichotomy.

17:28.681 --> 17:32.119
Oh, dichotomy, my ass.
I nearly died.
Look at my hospital file.

17:34.187 --> 17:36.156
Jesus. God.

17:36.189 --> 17:39.326
I don't think any of us wants
this to come to trial, do we?

17:39.359 --> 17:41.861
No, no.
No, we don't.

17:41.894 --> 17:44.697
So really, it's just a question
of the amount of money
we're gonna settle on.

17:44.731 --> 17:46.766
I'm sure you've got
a figure in mind.

17:46.799 --> 17:50.570
Well, Ann, you--
you can't put
a price on suffering.

17:50.603 --> 17:53.306
No.
But you can try.

17:53.340 --> 17:57.777
Let's just each of us
