36:14.640 --> 36:16.908
See the woman behind the desk?

36:18.544 --> 36:20.612
Okay,
she took Di's fingerprints.

36:20.646 --> 36:23.615
They're gonna give her
a permanent record, okay?

36:23.649 --> 36:26.652
Shit. Shit, shit, shit.
If they run her record
through a database,

36:26.685 --> 36:28.654
they're gonna come up with
the real Doug Rich's license.

36:28.687 --> 36:30.756
Okay, Doug Rich
is all over the Internet.

36:30.789 --> 36:32.858
You know how much time
you can do for identity theft?

36:32.891 --> 36:35.727
Vehicular manslaughter?
Okay, Cael.

36:35.761 --> 36:38.330
She will not get
a permanent record.
Parole violation.

36:38.364 --> 36:41.833
Practicing law
without a license.
I said I will deal with this.

36:41.867 --> 36:44.336
I don't want to go
to a foster home.

36:44.370 --> 36:46.805
You will not
go to foster care.
Okay, Sammy? I promise.

36:46.838 --> 36:49.275
Nothing bad's
gonna happen to you.

36:50.542 --> 36:52.578
I'll never let them
take you away.

36:52.611 --> 36:56.448
Nobody is gonna
split up this family.
You hear?

36:56.482 --> 37:01.287
What, are you--
Are you drunk?
A little bit.

37:01.320 --> 37:03.589
Shit, Dad.
I will take care of this.

37:05.824 --> 37:08.627
Are you the one that booked
my daughter, ma'am?

37:08.660 --> 37:12.498
'Cause I'm sure
you're familiar...

37:12.531 --> 37:15.534
with Malloy versus
the State of Louisiana.

37:15.567 --> 37:19.538
[ Buzzing ]
Oh, hold on.
Hold on, hold on.

37:19.571 --> 37:22.808
[ Line Ringing ]
...in prohibition
of-of marijuana use.

37:22.841 --> 37:25.311
Hi.
What do you want, baby?

37:26.378 --> 37:28.480
What?

37:28.514 --> 37:31.883
Are you all right?
Mom's on her way.

37:31.917 --> 37:35.321
Excuse me.
When you were out there,
did you see my husband?

37:36.755 --> 37:38.924
- What'd you do?
- Seven unpaid
parking tickets.

37:38.957 --> 37:41.860
No.
Dad.

37:41.893 --> 37:45.631
God forbid Richard should have
to interrupt his conference call
to bail his wife out of jail.

37:45.664 --> 37:47.466
What a colossal dick.
[ Whispering ]
Dad.

37:49.601 --> 37:52.671
I didn't know you smoked pot.
It wasn't mine.
It was Ken--

37:52.704 --> 37:55.541
Some kid hid it on Ken
and I had to take it from him...

37:55.574 --> 37:58.310
because there's no way
he could have done this
without blowin' us all to hell.

37:58.344 --> 38:00.379
So you threw yourself
on the grenade?

38:00.412 --> 38:03.949
Oh, baby girl.
I'm so sorry.

38:03.982 --> 38:06.084
I never wanted
any of this to happen.

38:06.117 --> 38:10.322
[ Sighs ]
I love you so much.

38:10.356 --> 38:12.524
Uh, I know that, Dad.

38:12.558 --> 38:14.593
[ Sobbing ]
I love you more
than all the world.

38:14.626 --> 38:17.429
[ Sobbing ]

38:17.463 --> 38:22.434
All I want is for you
to be able to do
anything you want to do.

38:22.468 --> 38:25.337
For the love of God,
go find the bathroom and
splash some water on your face.

38:25.371 --> 38:27.573
Okay, honey.

38:27.606 --> 38:29.475
I love you.
I know.

38:31.543 --> 38:35.046
Richard's never in his life
told our girls he loves them.

38:38.016 --> 38:41.119
[ Sighs ]

38:41.152 --> 38:43.389
[ Sniffs ]

38:55.801 --> 38:57.969
[ Woman ]
Right in here, ma'am.

38:59.405 --> 39:03.475
- He was a tall man.
- Who was?

39:03.509 --> 39:05.844
My assailant.
The fellow who stole my purse.

39:06.978 --> 39:08.947
Oh.

39:12.718 --> 39:16.555
He-He was a tall,
thin man. Dark hair.

39:16.588 --> 39:19.024
Bushy eyebrows.
Mmm, eyebrows.

39:19.057 --> 39:20.859
Small eyes.
Small.

39:20.892 --> 39:23.795
Crooked teeth.
Okay, hang on. Hang on.

39:23.829 --> 39:28.867
Gotta get these in, you know?
You want this to be good?

39:29.901 --> 39:31.169
Was it sunny?

39:31.202 --> 39:34.105
[ Chattering ]

39:41.580 --> 39:45.751
Mom.
Oh, hey, baby.

39:45.784 --> 39:47.819
So Dad's here.
He's filling out
some paperwork.

39:49.955 --> 39:52.858
Oh, shit.
[ Woman ]
Mrs. Rich?

39:54.225 --> 39:56.528
Hello, Officer.

39:56.562 --> 39:59.531
I can't tell you
how sorry I am about all this.

39:59.565 --> 40:04.636
I, uh--
I have the 800 cash...

40:04.670 --> 40:06.805
for your
clean and sober program.

40:06.838 --> 40:11.042
And there is also a little
somethin' in there for
your police retirement fund.

40:11.076 --> 40:13.745
Just--
Well, I'll take you
to her.

40:13.779 --> 40:16.181
I think she's
learned her lesson.

40:16.214 --> 40:18.149
And it seemed like
he was kind of retarded.

40:19.951 --> 40:23.154
Retarded?
Why didn't you say
he was retarded?

40:23.188 --> 40:28.126
- [ Eraser Rubbing ]
-It happened outside the station
just 15 minutes ago.

40:29.194 --> 40:30.161
Ken.

40:32.631 --> 40:34.666
- Hey.
- Oh, um--

40:36.067 --> 40:40.872
The eyes are a bit weird.
You have a go.

40:42.808 --> 40:45.043
I got started.

40:46.612 --> 40:48.947
[ Man ]
His wife is here.
She posted bail.

40:48.980 --> 40:51.917
Time pass slow in there,
don't it?

40:53.284 --> 40:55.754
It's like it stands still.

40:55.787 --> 40:59.157
Yeah.
Yeah.

40:59.190 --> 41:04.796
My friend Kay,
she used to sing to me,
make the time go.

41:04.830 --> 41:06.932
You know what she'd sing?
What?

41:08.166 --> 41:12.804
* Jesus loves me
This I know *

41:12.838 --> 41:15.974
* For the Bible
tells me so *

41:17.876 --> 41:22.080
* Little things
to him belong *
[ Sniffling ]

41:22.113 --> 41:26.818
* They are weak
But he is strong **

41:28.554 --> 41:32.157
[ Crying ]
We'd look up,

41:32.190 --> 41:35.126
and what do you know,
five minutes'd be gone.

41:37.262 --> 41:42.000
That's how you
break the day up--
in little pieces like that.

41:42.033 --> 41:45.804
[ Door Closes ]
Well, I ain't heard that song
since I was a little girl.

41:45.837 --> 41:48.239
Paperwork's done.

41:48.273 --> 41:51.677
Free as a bird.
Not you.

41:51.710 --> 41:53.879
Tell Richard
I won't forget this.

41:53.912 --> 41:55.981
[ Sobbing Quietly ]
It's okay, baby.

41:59.084 --> 42:01.887
Dad, where were you?

42:01.920 --> 42:06.625
Where's Ken?
He walked home about
15 minutes ago.

42:06.658 --> 42:08.894
[ Sighs ]
[ Woman ]
You'll be glad to know...

42:08.927 --> 42:11.597
we feel no need
to put this on
her permanent record.

42:11.630 --> 42:14.633
You know, with you-all
bein' so willing to
enroll her in our program,

42:14.666 --> 42:16.868
there's plenty of hope
for her to be rehabilitated.

42:16.902 --> 42:19.671
Well, thank you so much.

42:19.705 --> 42:23.742
Mr. Rich seems
a little stressed,
if you don't mind my saying.

42:28.246 --> 42:30.181
Thank you.

42:31.683 --> 42:33.619
[ Slurred ]
Baby--
[ Car Alarm Chirps ]

42:33.652 --> 42:35.754
you were
magnificent in there.

42:35.787 --> 42:39.791
Totally smooth, calm.
Above it all.

42:39.825 --> 42:42.193
- Like a queen.
- [ Panting ]
I can't do this.

42:42.227 --> 42:44.229
Ooh, I can't do this anymore.

42:44.262 --> 42:47.633
I can't do this anymore.
Hey, hey, hey.

42:47.666 --> 42:51.069
Hey. It's okay.
It's okay. It's okay.

42:51.102 --> 42:53.639
[ Dahlia Crying ]
[ Wayne Whispering ]
Hey.

42:56.174 --> 43:00.746
** [ Humming "Rock of Ages" ]

43:00.779 --> 43:05.684
Honey, stop humming.
[ Whispering ]
Hey.

43:05.717 --> 43:07.686
[ Man On TV ]
Oh, that was wonderful.

43:07.719 --> 43:10.155
Lars Mortenson
and the Alpine Cloggers.

43:10.188 --> 43:13.091
You know,
we certainly can't get enough
of the folk dances here.

43:13.124 --> 43:16.394
Next up, the Briggs Sisters.
Please don't go away.

43:16.427 --> 43:18.697
Hey, Daddy.
Hmm?

43:18.730 --> 43:20.331
Nurse called,
said she's gonna
be a little late.

43:23.101 --> 43:24.936
[ Labored Breathing ]
What the hell
are you watchin'?

43:24.970 --> 43:27.205
Day nurse put this on?

43:27.238 --> 43:30.208
Lame-ass polka shit.

43:32.243 --> 43:36.214
You must be sick as hell of
being cooped up in here all day.

43:39.985 --> 43:43.354
You must be dyin'
for some fresh air.
[ Inhales Deeply ]

43:46.091 --> 43:49.160
Oh, no, no.
No, don't tire yourself out.

43:49.194 --> 43:51.229
I got you.

43:59.204 --> 44:02.808
It's cold tonight.
Look at them stars, Daddy.

44:02.841 --> 44:07.045
How come y'all can see the stars
better when it's cold?

44:07.078 --> 44:10.181
When I was a kid,
I used to think that
the stars were made of ice.

44:10.215 --> 44:12.751
Do you remember that?
We'd go camping.

44:12.784 --> 44:15.420
You'd let me pretend
we were Indians.

44:15.453 --> 44:18.123
You gave us Indian names.
You were Big Elk.

44:18.156 --> 44:20.191
Remember what
you used to call me?

44:20.225 --> 44:23.128
That's right.
I was Little Bear.
[ Groans ]

44:25.897 --> 44:27.766
Earl?

44:29.968 --> 44:32.003
Earl?

44:34.806 --> 44:39.410
We'd set up our tent,
and you'd tell me the stories
about the Ridge Runner.

44:40.779 --> 44:42.781
[ Shivering ]

44:42.814 --> 44:44.950
Crazy Indian who lost his tribe,

44:44.983 --> 44:48.019
and he would haunt
these woods,
scalpin' little boys.

44:49.755 --> 44:52.758
And after you went to sleep,

44:56.261 --> 44:58.897
I would lie there so scared.
[ Crying ]

44:58.930 --> 45:02.067
But I never
made a sound.

45:02.100 --> 45:04.770
'Cause I wanted you to think
that I was so brave.

45:10.341 --> 45:14.312
[ Sobs ]
All I ever wanted to do was
to make you proud, Daddy.

45:17.382 --> 45:19.317
I'll always be
your brave little Indian.

45:19.350 --> 45:23.188
[ Bell Rings ]

45:23.221 --> 45:25.924
[ Sobbing ]

45:29.160 --> 45:31.930
I love you, Daddy.

45:34.332 --> 45:39.470
And I will carry you in my heart
till the day that I die.

45:39.504 --> 45:41.973
[ Gasping ]
Good-bye.

45:43.875 --> 45:45.877
[ Gasping ]
[ Ringing ]

45:45.911 --> 45:48.980
[ Groaning, Crying ]
[ Ringing ]

45:51.883 --> 45:55.253
[ Crying ]

45:55.286 --> 45:58.957
[ Bell Ringing ]
